  "tree": {
    "id": "root",
    "text": "Common Food Myths",
    "emoji": "🧐",
    "state": "emoji",
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "myth1",
        "text": "Myth 1: Only Fruit and Vegetables",
        "emoji": "🥦",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "p1",
            "text": "The human body needs to eat many different types of food to stay healthy.",
            "emoji": "🧬",
            "keywords": "different types, stay healthy",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2",
            "text": "The Chinese Food Guide Pagoda shows us what food we should eat.",
            "emoji": "🗼",
            "keywords": "Food Guide Pagoda",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p3",
            "text": "While fruit and vegetables are healthy choices, it is just as important to eat foods from other food groups.",
            "emoji": "🥛",
            "highlight": "While, just as",
            "keywords": "other food groups",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p4",
                "text": "Milk, for example, contains many nutrients and is good for our bones.",
                "emoji": "🦴",
                "highlight": "for example",
                "keywords": "nutrients, bones",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "p5",
                "text": "We should include milk or dairy products among the things we eat.",
                "emoji": "🧀",
                "highlight": "among",
                "keywords": "dairy products",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "myth2",
        "text": "Myth 2: Eating Fat Makes You Fat",
        "emoji": "🧈",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "p6",
            "text": "Eating fat is important for keeping us healthy.",
            "emoji": "🔋",
            "keywords": "fat, keeping healthy",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p7",
                "text": "It gives us energy and helps our body to take in nutrients.",
                "emoji": "⚡",
                "highlight": "and",
                "keywords": "energy, nutrients",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "p8",
            "text": "Not all fat makes us gain weight.",
            "emoji": "⚖️",
            "keywords": "gain weight",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p9",
                "text": "Some fat can even encourage our body to lose weight.",
                "emoji": "📉",
                "highlight": "even",
                "keywords": "lose weight",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "p10",
            "text": "It is necessary to include some, but not too much, fat in our food to help our body work well.",
            "emoji": "⚙️",
            "highlight": "but, not too much",
            "keywords": "work well",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "myth3",
        "text": "Myth 3: Eating Only What I Like",
        "emoji": "🍭",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "p11",
            "text": "When we are young, it might feel like we can just eat whatever we want!",
            "emoji": "👦",
            "highlight": "When, just, whatever",
            "keywords": "young, eat whatever",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p12",
                "text": "For example, sweets and fried foods taste delicious.",
                "emoji": "🍟",
                "highlight": "For example",
                "keywords": "sweets, fried foods",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "p13",
                "text": "But we cannot eat those foods alone.",
                "emoji": "🛑",
                "highlight": "But",
                "keywords": "not alone",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "p14",
            "text": "Eating balanced meals is very important when we are young.",
            "emoji": "🥗",
            "highlight": "when",
            "keywords": "balanced meals",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p15",
                "text": "It helps our body and brain to grow well.",
                "emoji": "🧠",
                "highlight": "and",
                "keywords": "grow well",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "p16",
            "text": "Bad eating habits may stay with us our whole life, so it is best to develop good eating habits early!",
            "emoji": "📅",
            "highlight": "so, it is best to",
            "keywords": "habits early",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
